er":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40214,"name":"Mohamed Chit","username":"mohamed.chit","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/d6d6ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-11-08T21:03:36.920Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi,\u003cbr\u003e\nI meant I do not use it in the second quad command, and it changes the result, before declaring the render target, transparency worked, after declaring the target, transparency was gone, even it was not used in the second quad.\u003cbr\u003e\nHaving multiple viewports is exactly identical to sample number 09: MultipleViewports.cpp\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Samples/09_MultipleViewports/MultipleViewports.cpp\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003ehttps://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Samples/09_MultipleViewports/MultipleViewports.cpp\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI believe if you just try the path renders i provided and the shaders, you will get the same result.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI hope if this an issue in Urho3d to be fixed, I like Urho3d, but this is a bit frustrating, especially it is not understood why it is happening. at least from my side.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-08T21:03:36.920Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":10,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":22,"readers_count":21,"score":9.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":6510,"topic_slug":"top-viewport-to-be-transparent-on-parent-big-viewport","display_username":"Mohamed Chit","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Samples/09_MultipleViewports/MultipleViewports.cpp","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/MultipleViewports.cpp at master · urho3d/Urho3D · GitHub","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1386,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40215,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-11-08T21:08:18.803Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYou don’t use color buffer filled by scene rendering, true. Are you certain you don’t use depth buffer? I’m not. Render paths are obscure thing, I have never really liked debugging them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe point is, your render paths are beyond complex and I have no clue what exactly they are doing.\u003cbr\u003e\nWhereas your initial task requires no render path modification at all.\u003cbr\u003e\nDefault render path should work just fine.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-08T21:08:18.803Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":11,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":23,"readers_count":22,"score":9.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":6510,"topic_slug":"top-viewport-to-be-transparent-on-parent-big-viewport","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"reply_to_user":{"username":"mohamed.chit","name":"Mohamed Chit","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/d6d6ee/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40216,"name":"Mohamed Chit","username":"mohamed.chit","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/d6d6ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-11-08T21:21:49.963Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI render the scene to the render target, then I use the render target as a texture in the second quad command.\u003cbr\u003e\nThe second quad command uses the blend \u003cstrong\u003eadd\u003c/strong\u003e, but it is not behaving this way.\u003cbr\u003e\nWhen I do not use a render target, the concept works. there is no clear explanation why this is happening.\u003cbr\u003e\nI am not using any depth information from the drawn scene in the render target, I get only the texture colors.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-08T21:21:49.963Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":12,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":23,"readers_count":22,"score":24.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":6510,"topic_slug":"top-viewport-to-be-transparent-on-parent-big-viewport","display_username":"Mohamed Chit","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1386,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40217,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-11-08T21:24:57.281Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYou are not using depth information explicitly, but it may be used by default. I don’t really remember all the defaults. I think every command uses depth information by default, but I may be wrong.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAlso, my previous question stands. How exactly do you render small viewport on top of parent viewport? I checked previous replies several times but I didn’t find an answer.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":14,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-08T21:30:13.149Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":13,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":9.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":6510,"topic_slug":"top-viewport-to-be-transparent-on-parent-big-viewport","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"reply_to_user":{"username":"mohamed.chit","name":"Mohamed Chit","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/d6d6ee/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40218,"name":"Mohamed Chit","username":"mohamed.chit","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/d6d6ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-11-08T21:31:21.508Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003efor the parent/child viewport, I use the renderer,\u003cbr\u003e\nI set the num of view to 2\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003erenderer-\u0026gt;SetNumViewports(2);\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethe parent has the index 0\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003erenderer-\u0026gt;SetViewport(0, main_viewport);\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethe child has the index 1\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003erenderer-\u0026gt;SetViewport(1, second_viewport);\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI tried as well between the first quad command and the second quad command to clear the depth buffer only on the viewport, that does not help as well.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":15,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-08T21:32:27.749Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":14,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":21,"readers_count":20,"score":19.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":6510,"topic_slug":"top-viewport-to-be-transparent-on-parent-big-viewport","display_username":"Mohamed Chit","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1386,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40219,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-11-08T21:39:50.527Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI see. I’ll think about it a bit more. BTW, have you tried actual “alpha” blend in that first render path in second quad command?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":16,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-08T21:39:50.527Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":15,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":18,"readers_count":17,"score":8.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":6510,"topic_slug":"top-viewport-to-be-transparent-on-parent-big-viewport","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"reply_to_user":{"username":"mohamed.chit","name":"Mohamed Chit","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/d6d6ee/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40220,"name":"Mohamed Chit","username":"mohamed.chit","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/d6d6ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-11-08T21:53:28.317Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI tried that already, it did not work.\u003cbr\u003e\nIn concept, I have provided the equation above, it shows how the two quad commands should make transparent result, it should work.\u003cbr\u003e\nFor now it works only without render target, but Using render target is making the problem for some reason.\u003cbr\u003e\nUsing two quad commands with blend \u003cstrong\u003emultiply\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003eadd\u003c/strong\u003e respectively should be correct.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":17,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-08T21:53:28.317Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":16,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":14.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":6510,"topic_slug":"top-viewport-to-be-transparent-on-parent-big-viewport","display_username":"Mohamed Chit","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1386,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40221,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-11-08T21:58:53.910Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"mohamed.chit\" data-post=\"17\" data-topic=\"6510\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/d6d6ee/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e mohamed.chit:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ebut Using render target is making the problem for some reason.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYep, I see the problem now. Render path evaluation is tricky thing that may depend on your exact hardware, application code and launch configuration. I may try to debug it later \u003cem\u003eif\u003c/em\u003e I reproduce this issue.\u003cbr\u003e\nTry debugging it yourself too, RenderDoc is quite easy to use. Doesn’t work on OpenGL 2 tho.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":18,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-08T21:58:53.910Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":17,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":4.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":6510,"topic_slug":"top-viewport-to-be-transparent-on-parent-big-viewport","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40226,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-11-09T09:55:36.761Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eSo, I have good news and bad news.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGood news is that I understand why it doesn’t work.\u003cbr\u003e\nBad news is that I have no clue what to do about it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou see, Urho has “render target substitution” mechanism.\u003cbr\u003e\nRender path, generally speaking, doesn’t always write into output texture directly.\u003cbr\u003e\nSometimes it chooses to use intermediate buffer.\u003cbr\u003e\nExact conditions are beyond my understanding.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo, you cannot expect “viewport” to contain anything reasonable at the beginning of render path.\u003cbr\u003e\nI don’t know if it was done to simplify things, or if it was intentional decision to isolate render paths so output of one render path does not affect another render path.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnyway, I don’t see how you can make it work with separate \u003ccode\u003eViewport\u003c/code\u003es.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou may consider using UIElement for 3D scene view to get what you want.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":19,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-09T09:56:23.168Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":17,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":19,"readers_count":18,"score":3.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":6510,"topic_slug":